quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  76,6,"a spring for God’s servants, which flows abundantly at their wish."
  76,7,"They fulfil their vows; they fear a day of widespread woes;"
  76,8,"they give food to the poor, the orphan, and the captive, though they love it themselves,"
  76,9,"saying, ‘We feed you for the sake of God alone: We seek neither recompense nor thanks from you."
  76,10,"We fear the Day of our Lord––a woefully grim Day.’"